  <guideline>Prefer the migration target's idiomatic patterns over a mechanical rename.
  A new-version idiom is often a different shape — e.g. an `Annotated` type instead of
  a decorator, a builder method instead of a class attribute, a context manager instead
  of a try/finally pair. Before finalizing a step, ask: "would a project written natively
  for the target version express it this way?" If not, revise. When the replacement
  pattern relies on general training knowledge rather than the gathered context, prefix
  the fix-step description with `Assumption:` so reviewers can verify.</guideline>
  <guideline>Order fix steps by dependency — changes that other changes depend on should come first.</guideline>
